WEBVTT

00:20.744 --> 00:22.746
[CRICKETS CHIRPING]

00:33.102 --> 00:34.310
[CAR ENGINE REVS]

00:34.344 --> 00:37.761
[UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING
ON CAR STEREO]

00:47.978 --> 00:49.290
JULIAN: I don't wanna be late.

00:49.773 --> 00:50.843
[CHUCKLES]

00:55.745 --> 00:56.815
OLIVIA: Oof!

00:59.404 --> 01:00.301
Take it.

01:00.819 --> 01:02.786
-No.
-Come on.

01:02.821 --> 01:04.271
No, I don't even
know what that is.

01:04.305 --> 01:06.411
It's just a little oxy.
Come on, it'll chill you out.

01:11.761 --> 01:13.970
Come on.

01:14.004 --> 01:16.731
Look, honestly, I'm only even
coming because you asked me to.

01:17.801 --> 01:18.940
Really, Julian?

01:18.975 --> 01:20.494
Where else would you
rather be right now?

01:20.528 --> 01:23.083
Literally, anywhere else
in the entire world than
where we're going.

01:23.117 --> 01:26.086
Come on. I just wanna have
some fun with you, okay?

01:26.810 --> 01:27.984
Just do it quick
like a Band-Aid.

01:28.018 --> 01:29.330
Stop, okay?

01:33.990 --> 01:35.233
[OLIVIA CHUCKLES]

01:37.718 --> 01:38.719
JULIAN: I have an idea.

01:39.996 --> 01:44.138
How about you just take
all of the pills by yourself?

01:45.243 --> 01:46.313
You're an asshole.

01:46.347 --> 01:49.109
It was a joke.
I'm fucking joking.

01:49.143 --> 01:53.320
Okay, well, then,
prove it then. Take it.

01:57.807 --> 01:58.842
Come on.

02:05.159 --> 02:06.816
Here.

02:06.850 --> 02:08.162
I'm driving. Are you serious?

02:08.197 --> 02:10.302
Just a sip,
it'll help you
wash it down.

02:11.545 --> 02:12.408
-No.
-Yes.

02:12.442 --> 02:13.926
We're almost
there anyways.
Come on.

02:13.961 --> 02:15.169
Are we?

02:16.205 --> 02:17.792
What exit do we
even get off at?

02:17.827 --> 02:19.104
Don't change the subject.

02:19.139 --> 02:22.590
I just want you to
have a little fun
for once, okay? Jeez!

02:22.625 --> 02:23.557
Come on.

02:28.389 --> 02:29.287
Another.

02:29.735 --> 02:30.598
No.

02:32.117 --> 02:34.050
Will you check on
the address for me, please?

02:34.084 --> 02:34.947
OLIVIA: Yeah, sure.

02:35.914 --> 02:37.778
Wrote it down here somewhere.

02:42.162 --> 02:43.853
How do you know this guy again?

02:44.405 --> 02:46.476
Uh, he's a coworker.

02:46.511 --> 02:49.203
Worked on a shoot together
a couple months ago.

02:50.135 --> 02:51.378
Cool.

02:51.412 --> 02:53.759
Yeah. And he also
likes playing poker too.

02:53.794 --> 02:56.728
Something that I think
you would be really good at.

02:56.762 --> 02:57.832
Try it.

02:58.454 --> 02:59.386
Maybe.

03:02.768 --> 03:07.773
But I would rather
spend my money on
what's underneath your seat.

03:09.154 --> 03:11.087
-What?
-What?

03:11.121 --> 03:12.916
Are you serious?

03:12.951 --> 03:14.504
What did you do?

03:16.541 --> 03:17.749
Oh, my God!

03:19.129 --> 03:21.304
When did you get this?

03:22.409 --> 03:24.721
JULIAN: Got it today.

03:24.756 --> 03:27.690
Oh, my God, Julian,
this is amazing!

03:27.724 --> 03:30.658
JULIAN: I needed
a break from writing,
so I took a walk downtown.

03:30.693 --> 03:33.282
I saw this really cool
camera store

03:33.316 --> 03:35.180
that I thought
you would like,

03:35.215 --> 03:37.251
so I went in
and I picked that up.

03:37.286 --> 03:40.289
Oh, my gosh,
thank you!
I love it.

03:43.878 --> 03:44.776
Say cheese.

03:44.810 --> 03:45.949
Be careful, okay?

03:47.054 --> 03:48.435
[CRASHING]

03:50.368 --> 03:51.610
[JULIAN SCREAMING]

03:53.647 --> 03:54.579
[CRASHING]

03:56.305 --> 03:58.307
[EMERGENCY VEHICLE
SIRENS WAILING]

07:27.550 --> 07:30.760
[JULIAN READING]

07:37.353 --> 07:38.596
OLIVIA: So, uh...

07:39.666 --> 07:41.771
I have to leave
to go to this

07:42.703 --> 07:44.222
half-day shoot thing that...

07:44.256 --> 07:45.499
JULIAN: Seeing open spaces...

07:45.534 --> 07:46.845
And then I'm gonna go
run some errands afterwards.

07:46.880 --> 07:49.330
[JULIAN READING]

07:49.365 --> 07:52.333
OLIVIA: Don't worry,
I'm not gonna go be gone
the entire day.

07:52.368 --> 07:54.163
JULIAN: Distracting
me sometimes.

07:54.197 --> 07:55.923
I've read online that
sometimes people develop...

07:55.958 --> 07:57.856
OLIVIA: You need me
to get anything?

07:57.891 --> 07:59.202
JULIAN: I've read
online that sometimes

07:59.237 --> 08:01.101
people develop panic attacks
or motion sickness,

08:01.135 --> 08:03.103
but I'm not sure how
that will mess with me.

08:03.137 --> 08:04.553
OLIVIA: Julian.

08:04.587 --> 08:05.692
JULIAN: I'm already
experiencing lots of
general panic

08:05.726 --> 08:06.796
-and sickness.
-Hello!

08:06.831 --> 08:08.557
What's up?

08:08.591 --> 08:10.904
JULIAN: Will it help me if I am
talking to other people
about it or something?

08:10.938 --> 08:14.321
I'm not sure if that's gonna
make a difference for me.

08:14.355 --> 08:16.530
This is not going very well.

08:16.565 --> 08:19.291
Prolonged exposure to
the VR headset is having

08:19.326 --> 08:21.501
-interesting effects
on my mind.
-Smile, babe!

08:25.574 --> 08:27.127
I hate it when you do that.

08:27.161 --> 08:28.024
Do what?

08:28.991 --> 08:31.752
"Do what?" That.
When you ignore me.

08:33.167 --> 08:36.205
I'm sorry, I just...
I had an idea for an article.

08:38.690 --> 08:40.796
I got preoccupied. I'm sorry.

08:40.830 --> 08:42.832
You should focus
more on me, babe.

08:43.557 --> 08:45.110
That's all I do.

08:47.354 --> 08:48.562
Good.

08:50.081 --> 08:52.221
I'll be back.
Do you need anything?

08:52.255 --> 08:55.155
No, I'm good.
See you later.

10:00.116 --> 10:01.048
You're late.

10:01.083 --> 10:03.223
Yeah, well, you're
a shitty drug dealer.

10:04.742 --> 10:07.952
I got out of the bar
at 6 a.m. this morning.

10:07.986 --> 10:10.748
Don't you get up early
for shoots or what?

10:10.782 --> 10:13.267
Yes, sometimes,
but I wasn't booked today.

10:13.302 --> 10:15.684
You're right. Today I am
a shitty drug dealer.

10:15.718 --> 10:16.926
I only have half
of what you want.

10:16.961 --> 10:19.860
What? Come on.
Where's the other half?

10:21.068 --> 10:23.692
Hey, where is
the other half?

10:25.072 --> 10:26.487
You're just gonna
have to trust me.

10:26.522 --> 10:28.179
Oh, yeah?
Why should I do that?

10:28.213 --> 10:30.112
Because I've always
been good to you.

10:32.977 --> 10:35.462
Yeah, Okay. But still,
what if I don't?

10:35.496 --> 10:38.707
Well, if you don't then you're
just gonna have to figure
that out for yourself, Hunter.

10:41.606 --> 10:43.194
All right, fine. What do
you want me to do?

10:43.228 --> 10:45.506
I have to run an errand,
and it won't take long.

10:45.541 --> 10:47.129
But it's downtown.

10:47.163 --> 10:48.371
Come on, Liv, seriously?

10:48.406 --> 10:50.166
I've been waiting all night
for these fucking things.

10:50.201 --> 10:52.375
So, you're just gonna
have to wait a little while
longer, okay?

10:52.410 --> 10:53.687
All right, fine.

10:53.722 --> 10:55.240
Give me the other half
you have now.

10:55.275 --> 10:56.276
Yeah?

11:10.600 --> 11:12.982
[HAPPY SONG PLAYING]

11:16.779 --> 11:20.231
JULIAN: I know I'm not
the easiest person
to be around maybe.

11:20.265 --> 11:24.338
I'm a human though,
and I'm bound to make
mistakes just like you.

11:24.373 --> 11:27.307
The good thing about us,
is we learn from our mistakes

11:27.341 --> 11:29.102
and we forgive each other.

11:29.136 --> 11:33.727
I want to keep making mistakes and learning with you for
a really long time, Olivia.

11:33.762 --> 11:34.832
I love you the most.

11:35.418 --> 11:36.488
Happy birthday.

12:10.868 --> 12:12.214
Hey, how are you?

12:12.248 --> 12:14.561
Hey, Sammy. I have
some winners for you.

12:14.595 --> 12:15.665
How's it going with you?

12:15.700 --> 12:18.772
I'm fine. Thank God.
One day at a time.

12:18.807 --> 12:20.049
I know what you mean.

12:22.534 --> 12:24.536
Did you get some new stuff in?
It looks different.

12:24.571 --> 12:25.675
No.

12:25.710 --> 12:28.471
Same here as last week.

12:28.506 --> 12:31.405
So, could I put
the money towards
as many pills as I can.

12:31.440 --> 12:32.786
No problem.

12:32.821 --> 12:34.512
Actually, can I get
a quick pic first?

12:34.546 --> 12:35.409
Okay.

12:46.869 --> 12:48.940
Here you go.
You are all set.

12:48.975 --> 12:50.493
Thanks, Sammy. You're the best.

12:50.528 --> 12:52.357
Thank you.
Have a good one.

12:52.392 --> 12:53.289
You too.

13:30.361 --> 13:33.053
[STRAINING]

13:34.814 --> 13:35.918
[THUDDING]

14:01.599 --> 14:02.772
Is that so hard?

14:02.807 --> 14:04.636
I didn't doubt you.

14:04.671 --> 14:08.054
-Your shoe's untied.
-Oh, yeah.

14:11.954 --> 14:13.749
So, tonight's the night, huh?

14:13.783 --> 14:14.715
What if it is?

14:14.750 --> 14:16.925
I don't know.
What if it is?

14:17.442 --> 14:18.788
If it is...

14:18.823 --> 14:21.032
I'd be a new woman.

14:21.067 --> 14:23.345
I'd be smart with it though,
I'd take the annuity.

14:24.415 --> 14:25.761
I'd be different.

14:25.795 --> 14:27.107
Really? How?

14:28.626 --> 14:30.386
How'd you be different?

14:30.421 --> 14:31.732
Would you quit?

14:31.767 --> 14:36.427
I don't know about that.
Maybe. Maybe not.

14:36.461 --> 14:39.499
I'd definitely quit bartending
though, get a nice house,

14:39.533 --> 14:40.638
a few nice cars.

14:40.672 --> 14:42.398
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

14:42.433 --> 14:46.471
Those are literally
the worst things you can do
after winning the lottery.

14:46.506 --> 14:49.095
I bet you'd take
the cash up front, huh?

14:49.129 --> 14:50.993
Yeah, I probably would
take the cash.

14:51.028 --> 14:52.408
[PHONE VIBRATING]

14:52.443 --> 14:54.514
You know what else
I'd do though, if I
won right now?

14:55.204 --> 14:56.102
What?

14:56.896 --> 14:58.449
I'd go get some tacos.

14:58.967 --> 15:00.623
You want some tacos?

15:00.658 --> 15:02.315
[PHONE CONTINUES
VIBRATING]

15:02.902 --> 15:04.420
Do you need to get that?

15:04.455 --> 15:05.421
Nah.

15:09.978 --> 15:10.979
[CAMERA CLICKS]

15:11.013 --> 15:12.290
[OLIVIA CHUCKLES]

15:17.295 --> 15:18.365
Can I see it?

15:18.987 --> 15:20.333
You can keep it.

15:20.367 --> 15:21.990
Oh, I can keep it.

15:22.404 --> 15:23.405
Mmm-hmm.

15:23.439 --> 15:25.096
I can keep it.

15:25.131 --> 15:26.408
All right, I gotta go.

15:28.582 --> 15:29.687
What are you...

15:29.721 --> 15:31.309
What are you doing tonight?

15:31.931 --> 15:33.173
Don't you remember?

15:33.208 --> 15:34.968
Oh, yeah, that's right.

15:35.003 --> 15:36.176
Good luck.

15:36.211 --> 15:39.145
Don't let it
change you. [CHUCKLES]

16:27.917 --> 16:30.058
Julian, what is this?

16:31.749 --> 16:32.715
Julian?

16:34.027 --> 16:35.511
Holy shit.

16:35.546 --> 16:40.516
Hey, wake up. Wake up. Hey. Hey.Oh, my God. Are you okay?

16:41.552 --> 16:42.656
Hi.

16:42.691 --> 16:45.107
Yes. Yeah, I just got here.
What... What happened?

16:45.142 --> 16:46.798
Slipped off the stool.

16:46.833 --> 16:48.179
Well, can you...
Can you move?

16:48.697 --> 16:49.767
I tried earlier.

16:49.801 --> 16:52.770
Okay, well, let's try
again together, all right?

16:52.804 --> 16:55.255
Maybe... Maybe
I shouldn't move.

16:55.290 --> 16:56.429
Maybe we should
call a doctor.

16:56.463 --> 16:57.809
No, no, no, it's gonna
be fine, all right?

16:57.844 --> 17:00.398
Let's... Let's do it on
the count of three, all right?

17:00.433 --> 17:01.296
Ready?

17:01.882 --> 17:04.264
One, two,

17:05.748 --> 17:06.611
three.

17:07.440 --> 17:08.475
No!

17:09.580 --> 17:11.409
OLIVIA:
Okay. Okay.

17:12.721 --> 17:14.205
Are you okay?

17:18.037 --> 17:19.452
Ooh, you hit your head
pretty bad there.

17:19.486 --> 17:21.592
I'm gonna go
get the first aid kit.

17:21.626 --> 17:24.526
And I'm gonna get rid of
this stupid step stool.

17:53.279 --> 17:54.832
I'm sorry. I should have
just stayed home.

17:54.866 --> 17:56.178
I shouldn't have gone out.

18:00.079 --> 18:02.771
If you stayed home,
I wouldn't have been
able to surprise you.

18:05.153 --> 18:06.568
This was a terrible
surprise, Julian.

18:06.602 --> 18:07.569
[LAUGHS]

18:08.294 --> 18:10.158
You know what I mean.

18:10.192 --> 18:11.918
Did you see the kitchen?

18:11.952 --> 18:13.506
Yeah, I did.

18:14.886 --> 18:16.612
And I read
your card too.

18:18.235 --> 18:20.064
It was really
sweet of you.

18:20.099 --> 18:21.341
I love you.

18:22.756 --> 18:24.103
I love you too.

18:25.690 --> 18:29.280
Did you get the pills?
I'm almost out.

18:29.901 --> 18:33.042
Um, no, no, I...

18:33.077 --> 18:35.528
You know, I went there,
but they were...
they were closed,

18:35.562 --> 18:38.393
which was weird,
because they're...
They're never closed. But...

18:39.566 --> 18:41.534
You know, I stuck around
for a while, to wait,

18:41.568 --> 18:43.915
to see if anybody showed up,
and nobody did, so...

18:45.676 --> 18:46.884
I just left.

18:48.092 --> 18:50.163
Well, tomorrow can you
please pick them up?

18:50.198 --> 18:52.165
I don't want to run out.

18:52.200 --> 18:54.443
Maybe you should
get off of them, you know,

18:54.478 --> 18:57.964
I mean, they can't
be good for you.

18:57.998 --> 19:00.173
Maybe this can be
your last refill.

19:02.210 --> 19:04.315
I don't know
about that.

19:07.146 --> 19:08.871
Why would you say
something like that?

19:08.906 --> 19:11.322
I don't know,
you've been on it for a while,
and that can't be good, right?

19:11.840 --> 19:13.531
And...

19:13.566 --> 19:15.809
I mean, look at you,
you scared the shit out of me.

19:15.844 --> 19:18.778
Just pick them up tomorrow,
we can talk about it, okay?

19:20.883 --> 19:22.126
I want to help you.

19:22.161 --> 19:23.610
Look, you're already
helping me.

19:27.407 --> 19:28.753
I'll be right back.

19:32.240 --> 19:33.379
Hold...

19:34.242 --> 19:35.691
that, right there.

19:47.393 --> 19:49.326
-Birthday in bed?
-[LAUGHS]

19:51.086 --> 19:52.363
Let's do it.

20:01.338 --> 20:02.615
Happy birthday, Olivia.

20:03.719 --> 20:04.755
I love you.

20:09.380 --> 20:10.830
I love you too.

20:12.003 --> 20:14.005
[LAUGHING]

20:21.875 --> 20:23.774
[LAUGHING]

20:24.775 --> 20:25.707
What?

20:27.122 --> 20:28.434
Is there something
on my face?

20:28.468 --> 20:29.538
[LAUGHS]

20:30.436 --> 20:31.747
No, you look great.

20:31.782 --> 20:32.748
-Thank you.
-Mmm-hmm.

20:32.783 --> 20:35.061
[LAUGHING]

20:35.095 --> 20:36.614
Oh... all over you.

20:36.649 --> 20:38.582
Yeah, well,
you put it on me.

20:38.616 --> 20:40.308
Sorry, wait.
Let me just...

21:02.675 --> 21:04.711
JULIAN: I like
the grocery store.

21:08.784 --> 21:11.339
I get to choose
each ingredient.

21:11.373 --> 21:13.720
AUTOMATED VOICE: Thank you for shopping with us.

21:15.204 --> 21:17.552
[CAR ALARM BLARING]

21:25.284 --> 21:26.215
What?

21:26.250 --> 21:27.527
-[KEY FOB BEEPS]
-[ALARM STOPS]

21:27.562 --> 21:30.565
-[CRASHING]
-[EMERGENCY VEHICLE SIRENS]

21:35.259 --> 21:36.743
It's not that I hate cars.

21:36.778 --> 21:41.300
It's just that
after the accident
happened,

21:41.334 --> 21:43.198
it's hard for me
to trust them.

21:43.232 --> 21:47.064
Or it's hard to
trust myself in them.

21:47.651 --> 21:49.342
I don't know exactly.

22:08.568 --> 22:12.158
♪ I feel creepy all the time

22:12.192 --> 22:17.819
♪ 'Cause I like everybody
More than they like me

22:17.853 --> 22:23.549
♪ I know your feelings
And I make them rhyme

22:23.583 --> 22:28.519
♪ I know your feelings
And I make them rhyme

22:36.424 --> 22:40.911
♪ It's getting darker
Every day

22:40.945 --> 22:46.572
♪ And everyone is pushing me Out of the sun's way

22:46.606 --> 22:51.370
♪ I just wanna see the light

22:51.404 --> 22:55.166
♪ I just wanna see the light

23:06.039 --> 23:08.628
♪ What do you think

23:08.663 --> 23:12.011
♪ Of leaving Earth
And everyone we know

23:14.462 --> 23:19.605
♪ We can go anytime you want

23:19.639 --> 23:22.401
♪ Just let me know

23:48.150 --> 23:49.669
-Hey.
-[GASPS]

23:49.704 --> 23:51.291
What are you doing here?

23:51.326 --> 23:53.846
Oh, just running some errands.

23:53.880 --> 23:55.572
Never seen you in this
neighborhood before.

23:55.606 --> 23:59.161
Oh, yeah, yeah.
We've been to that park
down the street a few times.

23:59.196 --> 24:00.680
Yeah.

24:00.715 --> 24:02.199
I guess that's true, um...

24:03.545 --> 24:07.929
Well, hey, it was great
running into you, but, uh...

24:07.963 --> 24:10.656
I'm pretty busy,
so I better get going.

24:15.212 --> 24:17.145
Hey, is that a new dress?

24:17.179 --> 24:18.905
It's relatively new,
I guess.

24:18.940 --> 24:20.424
Yeah, it looks good.

24:20.459 --> 24:22.115
You notice a dress
like that.

24:22.150 --> 24:23.185
Thanks.

24:23.910 --> 24:24.808
Hey, uh...

24:24.842 --> 24:26.499
So, I know you got
some pills in there,

24:26.534 --> 24:27.535
you mind if I grab a few?

24:27.569 --> 24:29.571
-Are you already out?
-Yeah.

24:29.606 --> 24:31.055
I just need a few.

24:33.264 --> 24:34.956
I can't sell you these.

24:34.990 --> 24:36.198
You always sell to me.

24:36.233 --> 24:38.131
Yeah, but these are not for you,they're for somebody else.

24:39.167 --> 24:40.582
Yeah, I get that, but look,

24:40.617 --> 24:42.550
I'll pay you double
what I normally do.

24:42.584 --> 24:43.965
I just really need
a few right now.

24:43.999 --> 24:45.622
All right. Well, that was
really hard to turn down, yeah,

24:45.656 --> 24:47.347
but I can't
sell you these.
I'm sorry.

24:47.382 --> 24:49.211
Come on. What are they,
for your fucking boyfriend
or something?

24:49.246 --> 24:51.697
Yes, know what?
They're for my fucking
boyfriend, all right? Julian.

24:54.907 --> 24:56.253
Who's Julian?

24:56.287 --> 24:58.945
I just told you,
he's my boyfriend,
and he actually needs them.

25:10.888 --> 25:12.925
So, you never told me
you had a boyfriend.

25:13.822 --> 25:15.548
Why didn't you tell me?

25:15.583 --> 25:17.136
I don't know.
It just never came up.

25:17.170 --> 25:19.345
It's not like we're
super close, you know?

25:19.379 --> 25:22.106
What are you talking about?
We see each other, like,
a few times a week.

25:22.141 --> 25:23.936
How could you not tell me
you had a boyfriend?

25:23.970 --> 25:25.731
I just never did.

25:25.765 --> 25:28.734
Why is it such a big deal?
You're getting really weird.

25:31.944 --> 25:34.118
You're right, you know,
it's not a big deal, it's not.

25:35.948 --> 25:38.537
Look, could you
please just give me
a few pills, all right?

25:38.571 --> 25:40.124
You can use more money
for scratchers.

25:40.159 --> 25:41.919
I just... I'm really
desperate right now...

25:41.954 --> 25:43.956
I don't want to
keep wasting money
on these things.

25:43.990 --> 25:46.406
Nobody ever
wins them anyway.

25:46.441 --> 25:48.167
Actually, some people do.

25:48.201 --> 25:49.133
Then you know what happens?

25:49.168 --> 25:50.997
They gamble it all away
in Atlantic City.

25:53.103 --> 25:55.346
So, what'd you actually
end up doing the other night?

25:56.485 --> 25:58.211
Not going to
Atlantic City.

25:58.246 --> 25:59.937
Okay, so what'd you doing?

25:59.972 --> 26:00.800
I went home.

26:00.835 --> 26:02.353
-You went home?
-Yeah.

26:02.388 --> 26:04.045
Why, your boyfriend
doesn't let you hang out
with anybody else?

26:04.079 --> 26:05.736
What is with you today?
You're being rude.

26:05.771 --> 26:09.153
Me? What's with you?
You're acting like I'm
bothering you or something.

26:11.017 --> 26:13.295
I'm sorry, I'm just
stressed out.

26:13.330 --> 26:15.090
Why? Why are you
stressed out?

26:15.125 --> 26:17.921
I went home the other night
and I found Julian bleeding
on the floor, okay?

26:19.232 --> 26:20.268
What happened to him?

26:22.201 --> 26:25.238
He slipped off
a step stool in our bedroom
and split his head open.

26:25.273 --> 26:27.033
You guys live together?

26:27.068 --> 26:29.588
What the fuck, Hunter?
Yes, we live together.

26:31.072 --> 26:34.351
You know what?
I knew this
was a mistake.

26:34.385 --> 26:39.252
Wait... It's not
a mistake, all right?
Just sit down.

26:39.287 --> 26:41.047
Just sit down, please.

26:42.324 --> 26:44.395
All right, we're friends,
okay?

26:45.396 --> 26:46.950
You can talk to me,
what happened?

26:48.503 --> 26:49.884
Is he dead?

26:50.885 --> 26:52.300
First, I thought he was.

26:52.334 --> 26:55.855
He was just lying on the floor
with his eyes closed.

26:57.374 --> 26:58.478
So, he's not dead?

26:58.513 --> 26:59.825
No, he's not dead.

27:01.550 --> 27:02.931
We talked and...

27:04.105 --> 27:06.452
I think I'm gonna help him
get better.

27:06.486 --> 27:08.661
Well, if you want him
to get better,
Liv, just give me the pills.

27:08.696 --> 27:10.663
No, Hunter,
these are his last ones.

27:12.527 --> 27:13.977
Look, I should
tell you something.

27:15.461 --> 27:17.981
The reason I've been spending
so much time with you is...

27:18.015 --> 27:20.328
...because we understand
each other.

27:20.362 --> 27:21.536
No. It's because...

27:21.570 --> 27:23.331
It's because you use the money
I pay you for gambling.

27:23.365 --> 27:26.817
No, it's because I needed
somebody to be outside with.

27:27.956 --> 27:29.509
What?

27:29.544 --> 27:31.891
Couple months ago,
Julian and I got
into a car accident.

27:31.926 --> 27:35.136
And... now he doesn't like
to go outside.

27:36.171 --> 27:38.208
And I'm over it.
But he isn't now,

27:38.242 --> 27:41.038
and I don't know,
I guess I just needed somebody

27:41.073 --> 27:42.177
to hang out with.

27:45.215 --> 27:46.665
But now it's over

27:46.699 --> 27:48.667
'cause there aren't gonna be
any more pills.

27:48.701 --> 27:50.910
No more pills?
What are you saying?

27:52.153 --> 27:54.327
I'm saying that I'm gonna
help Julian get better.

27:54.362 --> 27:56.295
And I don't need
to keep seeing you
anymore.

28:02.335 --> 28:03.336
I should go.

28:05.166 --> 28:06.892
Where you going?

28:06.926 --> 28:10.343
Guess what? Julian,
he's never gonna get better,
all right?

28:10.378 --> 28:11.517
You know that, don't you?

28:11.551 --> 28:14.313
So, guess what, sweetheart?
You kind of do need me.

28:14.347 --> 28:16.211
I was stupid to think
you would understand.

28:17.523 --> 28:20.491
You know what? You can take 'em.

28:20.526 --> 28:22.977
You're just a lowlife
I hung out with
'cause I was bored.

28:23.011 --> 28:24.772
You're just a fucking tease.

28:39.200 --> 28:40.408
[HEART BEATING]

28:40.442 --> 28:43.066
JULIAN: Going outside
is an uneasy feeling now.

28:49.037 --> 28:51.074
I don't want a perfect life.

28:51.108 --> 28:53.732
I just want to stop neglecting my chance to have one.

28:55.354 --> 28:56.493
I wanna be there for Liv.

28:56.527 --> 28:59.013
And I want to support her
the way she supports me.

29:05.157 --> 29:07.124
Maybe if I could learn
how to be safe again,

29:07.159 --> 29:08.022
I can save us.

29:10.507 --> 29:11.784
JULIAN: Got it today.

29:11.819 --> 29:14.166
[INDISTINCT VOICES]

29:14.200 --> 29:15.201
JULIAN: What?

29:15.236 --> 29:16.651
[STATIC NOISES,
INDISTINCT VOICES CONTINUE]

29:16.685 --> 29:18.549
JULIAN:
So, I took a walk downtown.

29:18.584 --> 29:20.862
I saw this really cool
camera store

29:20.897 --> 29:22.933
that I thought
you would like,

29:22.968 --> 29:24.901
so I went in
and I picked that up.

29:24.935 --> 29:27.904
OLIVIA: Oh, my God...
I love it.

29:28.697 --> 29:29.560
Take it.

29:31.079 --> 29:31.942
[GRUNTS]

29:33.426 --> 29:35.808
[HEART BEATING CONTINUES]

29:55.069 --> 29:56.139
OLIVIA: [STATICKY] Um...

29:58.727 --> 29:59.590
No.

30:00.729 --> 30:01.592
No. I, uh...

30:07.702 --> 30:08.737
[STATICKY]
No, I went there,

30:08.772 --> 30:10.222
but they were...
They were closed.

30:16.055 --> 30:19.921
JULIAN:
I'm good. My mind's fine.
I'm good.

30:21.509 --> 30:23.166
[OLIVIA'S VOICE ECHOING]
I wanna help you.

30:25.202 --> 30:27.032
JULIAN: This is it.
This is as bad as it gets.

30:27.066 --> 30:28.412
And then it'll be over.

30:28.447 --> 30:30.414
[OLIVIA'S VOICE ECHOING]
Really, Julian?

30:30.449 --> 30:31.519
Stupid.

30:32.692 --> 30:35.074
So stupid thinking
it wouldn't affect me anyway.

30:35.764 --> 30:38.319
What if this... How could...

30:38.353 --> 30:40.114
This couldn't last forever,
could it?

30:46.534 --> 30:47.880
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

30:47.915 --> 30:49.675
OLIVIA: Maybe
you should get off
of them, you know.

30:49.709 --> 30:53.437
I mean, they can't
be good for you.

31:00.859 --> 31:01.894
[VOICE ECHOING] Julian?

31:06.140 --> 31:07.003
[GRUNTS]

31:11.524 --> 31:13.630
[PHONE RINGING]

31:13.664 --> 31:16.012
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

31:16.909 --> 31:18.428
-[PHONE BEEPS]
-Hey, where are you?

31:19.498 --> 31:20.361
